        • dbObjectSynonym
          String dbObjectSynonym
          The DB object synonym; optional, null when missing.
        • dbObjectTermId
          TermId dbObjectTermId
          The TermId of the database object being annotated. Includes both the "db" (which is the first column of the GO annotation file) as well as the dbObjectId (which is the second column in the GO annotation file). Note that GO is inconsistent, and sometimes the dbObjectId column also includes the database, e.g., the first two columns are "MGI","MGI:1918911". The constructor of this class sorts things out.
        • dbObjectType
          String dbObjectType
          The DB object type, e.g., "protein".

          Evidence code, e.g., "IMP".

          Gene product form ID; ; optional, null when missing.
        • goId
          TermId goId
          GO ID, e.g., "GO:0003993".
        • negated
          boolean negated
        • qualifier
          GoQualifier qualifier
          Optional, e.g., "NOT"; optional, null when missing.
        • taxons
          List<String> taxons
          Taxon(s), of cardinality 1 or 2.
        • with
          String with
          With (or) From, e.g., "GO:0000346"; optional, null when missing.
